transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Olivia speaking.

Speaker 2: Who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 1: This message has been transcribed. One moment while I notify the caller.

Speaker 2: Hello? Hello?

Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. I already said all of this and then...

Speaker 2: Oh, I didn't hear you.

Speaker 1: Yes, well, that's because you have a service set up so that once the phone picks up,

Speaker 2: somebody will say hello and then your Apple device, it has an introduction that says,

Speaker 1: we need to wait on hold to speak with you. But you called us, Jamie.

Speaker 2: Yes, ma'am, I did.

Speaker 1: You did. So yeah, you might want to update your phone service.

Speaker 2: Anyway, how can I help you today?

Speaker 1: I need to cancel my account.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I can help you with that. Okay, what's your date of birth?

Speaker 1: January 4, 79.

Speaker 2: And you're located at 558 Nelson Lane, Benton, Kentucky?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay. And this refill from today, would you like to receive it?

Speaker 1: No, if you can cancel it.

Speaker 2: Okay. So I just canceled and refunded that order.

Speaker 1: So you won't receive it, but you will see that refund within these next few days.

Speaker 2: And if you don't want to receive regular refills with your prescription,

Speaker 1: you certainly don't have to.

Speaker 2: You always have the option to place your prescription on hold for up to six months

Speaker 1: at a time just because six months is when the prescription would expire

Speaker 2: if we didn't refill it.

Speaker 1: And the way that would work is whenever you are ready to order, if it is before then,

Speaker 2: you just have to give us a call to place the order yourself.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Great. All right.

Speaker 1: So, yeah, if you need anything before August 11, just give us a call at this number,

Speaker 2: Monday through Friday, 8 to 5 Pacific.

Speaker 1: We're always here.

Speaker 2: And otherwise, your prescription is on hold.

Speaker 1: All right. Thank you much.

Speaker 2: Thank you, Jamie.

Speaker 1: Have a great day.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Okay. Thanks. Bye.
